node.text:
A little heartwarming content to make you smile. 🐶 

“Driving across America in our camper van we found this big boy in the middle of a country highway who desperately needed to be rescued or risked getting hit by a car. That was the first and only thing that crossed our minds when we stopped. Fast forward 3 months and our Yorkie and rescued English Mastiff are best friends! The missing link we didn’t know we needed!” 

📹: @asunnshine #smile #heartwarming #animals #love

node.text: The respiratory system of a Brazilian Skipper caterpillar in action. Their translucent skin makes this possible to see. As seen in the video, oxygen makes way to their tissues by the trachea. Air is pumped into the trachea, oxygen is taken in and carbon dioxide is pushed out #science #biology #caterpillar #anatomy #breathing (via science.feed)
